10/05/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Zeljka Antunovic, the acting leader of the Social Democratic Party, officially announced her candidacy Wednesday (May 9th) for the post of chairman. 
The main opposition party is expected to hold an extraordinary congress on June 2nd to fill the position, following the death of Ivica Racan. 
He died of cancer on April 30th. 
Local press reports suggest other likely candidates are party chief economist Ljubo Jurcic, Zagreb Mayor Milan Bandic, and Velika Gorica Mayor Tonino Picula. 
(Vecernji list, Poslovni dnevnik - 10/05/07; HRT - 09/05/07)
